                            <comment id="13432189" author="kkrugler" created="Thu, 9 Aug 2012 21:45:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi John - I tried this with trunk, and it works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, it&apos;s true that XHTMLDowngradeHandler will uppercase the element names, but then DefaultHtmlMapper.mapSafeElement() lower-cases them (I know, seems odd to me too). So the comparison works, and I see the expected output.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m adding a test case to validate behavior, at least for a simple &amp;lt;ul&amp;gt;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;xxx&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/ul&amp;gt; example.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
